ORLANDO Pirates defender Innocent Maela has apologized to the Bucs faithful for his error against Black Leopards. The left-back scored an own goal from a corner that he had conceded when his header came off the post. It was just the start Leopards needed and they quickly doubled their lead to drive home the advantage. Bucs eventually suffered their second defeat of the season. Maela took to social media to apologise for his erratic performance. “Disappointing match yesterday, simply not good enough,” Maela Tweeted. “I take full responsibility for my mistakes and actions leading up to the first goal. I apologize buccaneers. We promise to be better.”  